To install Video wall, dependencies, run:

sudo apt install git make gcc libx11-dev

git push https://github.com/mmhobi7/xwinwrap.git

cd xwinwrap
make
sudo make install

Image wallpaper- It will be in "$HOME/.local/share/nautilus/scripts/". To put any background image
with right click on the image, and Scripts, tab /Image wallpaper,
click to put on wallpaper, and also be added to the history list.

To (Speech recognition), you should add keyboard shortcuts
sh /usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/actions/w_m-speech-reco.sh.

And the lanucher for gnome-panel is here:
nautilus /usr/share/wallpaper_manager/w_m/app-panel/w_m-speech-reco.sh-1.desktop
Drag and drop on gnome-panel.

Use:
imagemagick (image manipulation programs),
sox (Swiss army knife of sound processing),
xsel (command-line tool to access X clipboard and selection buffers),
xscreensaver (Automatic screensaver for X),
mplayer (movie player for Unix-like systems),
pulseaudio (PulseAudio Volume Control),
original-awk (The original awk described in "The AWK Programming Language"),
pkexec (graphical frontend to su),
curl (Get a file from an HTTP, HTTPS or FTP server),
xscreensaver (Automatic screensaver for X),
shantz-xwinwrap (Stick apps to your desktop background.):

sudo apt-get install xplanet zenity imagemagick bc wget dbus-x11 gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1 gsettings-desktop-schemas nautilus python3-gi mplayer xscreensaver pkexec xsel python3 curl


