Functions:

 Change wallpaper:
 To put a random image from a specified directory as background
 screen.

 Previous image:
 Put the image background before the current.

 Next image:
 Set the background image after the current, if launched
 previous image previously, you can return to it was, with
 this option.

 Favorites ...:

 Save on Favorites:
 Track the uri of wallpaper, in the command:
 "gsettings get org.gnome.desktop.background picture-uri file :///"
 And create a list called: buenas_imágenes, with the images your
 keep. As a list of favorites.

 Put of Favorites:
 To put a random picture, everything on the list
 "Buenas_imagenes" as wallpaper.

 List favorites:
 Open a dialogue with all that is in the list "buenas_imágenes" and
 selecting double click, or click and OK, will be as wallpaper.

 Favorites viewer:
 Open all favorite images with the application eog (gnome viewer)

 Xml of favorites:
 Create a rotating wallpaper, images stored

 Remove from favorites: Removes favorites (the current fund)

 Edit of categories: Edit Lists

 By date, favorites: Use databases, saved with date

 Categories:
 Give the options to save in categories, list, and seeing launch
 Categories.
 List, you see favorite pictures stored list.
 Launch, puts a random picture from the category you choose.
 View, open all favorite images with the application eog (gnome
 viewer) where we see of many applications with
 our images as a slideshow, Open with, or Set as background
 desk. Although not contained in the history of the program, since only
 work when execute Wallpaper-Manager, you can, add to history, in the app
 indicator: ~*History ; include in history 
 Remove from categories (the current fund). Edit lists. And,
 By date, categories, and, My personal tags: (create your own)

 The categories are: animals, art, autos_motos, colors, crops_circles,
 Digital, buildings, space, films, mystics, music, ocean, scenery,
 Plants ríos_lagos, software, technology.

 History:
 List History: Lists the last 100 images that have been background
 desktop, using wallpaper manager.
 View History: Opens the history list with lightweight viewer wallpaper-gallery.py
 Include the history: For use when a program puts a background
 and we have it listed to get back to that image. And, Data by date

 All images:
 Create a file, which combines all saved data
 files "Categories" and "Favorites" to launch options
 Put of All images, View images, or images xml (revolving fund)
 and Edit data base with Gedit
 Put in the grub2: Puts the current wallpaper in the background of grub2
 Open image... Select a particular image file
 Open xml folder: Select a folder to a revolving fund
 Launch of this folder: Change the background for one another in the same folder
 Same directory image: Throwing image directory within ~/Pictures, which is
 the wallpaper if it is in a subdirectory, if not the same as, Launch of this folder.
 Save, or use folders: Give, Save, Use or Delete, path folders, if Use, Offers: View,
 Slideshow, Launch, List or XML, the content, paths to the folders
 Same folder xml
 Video Wallpaper: Wallpaper animated, with videos, screensavers, or, the web camera
 Nasa wallpaper: download nasa website astronomical images
 and puts desktop background
 Image from NatGeo: Download National Geogrphic site, an image, in several
 given categories to choose from.
 Image from google, by terms: Download images from a web search result
 Current image of the planet: Download "world_sunlight_map" Opentopia.com picture
 satellite of the globe, in real time, and updated hourly.
 Google search by image: Open the wallaper file, in the default browser, google search by images. 


 Special image:
 Save an image as favorite. Offers the function store, or activate
 your special picture.

 Report current picture:
 Sends a notification notify-send with the name of the wallpaper
 current.

 Open place:
 Launch the file browser, nautilus, selecting the file
 this as background image

 Slideshows:
 Slideshows of categories, Slideshows of favorites,
 Slideshows of current place y Open a Slideshows folder

 Display Mode:
 Change the scaling mode to display the wallpaper: Zoom, Centered
 Scaled, Wallpaper, Stretched

 Color of background: Pick color background, to choose a color
 primary (primary color is transparency, and unlike
 images with the resolution on the monitor)
 Natural Option to change primary color whit the image color tone, 
 with the command: _GNOME_BACKGROUND_REPRESENTATIVE_COLORS
 also: Add colors, colors List, Edit list. And save
 Secondary color (secondary color is the primary color degrade over)
 Choose secondary, Vertical Secondary, Secondary horizontal, and Solid.

 Edit image:
 Invert Colors
 White and black
 Write the picture
 Rotate clock
 Rotate anti clock
 Rotate invert

 Xscreensaver:
 Deactivate screensaver
 Activate screensaver
 Start screensaver
 screensaver next
 screensaver prev
 Pic screensaver
 Save on Favorites
 List Favorites
 Preferences
 If this is the first time you throw it you should run the function
 Preferences and two dialog boxes will open, accept two. And that's all

 Refresh List:
 Create the text file, with the path of all the images in the directory ~/Pictures.
 Text to be created, just do it once to continue using it with the same images as
 contained in, while
 Do not change the names or location. When you make a change to
 the image folder, you should toss Refresh List, to be reload the data.

 And speech recognition function
